    "body": "@xxxZedxxx @davux \r\n\r\nFor the dev mode, geth will choose clique algorithm as default consensus engine and enable mining implicitly. \r\n\r\nFor the clique algorithm, it has a configuration parameter called `Period`, which is used to indicate how often to create a block. In the dev mode, the default value for Period is 0, it means that a new block will be created only after the geth node receives the transaction. So it is the reason for `Block sealing failed err=\"waiting for transactions\"`\r\n\r\nBut you can specify the Period via `dev.Period` CLI flag explicitly by yourselves.\r\n\r\nAnd regarding the `miner.start` returning `null`. The return type is error, so it represents no error happened.\r\n\r\n",
